messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Yes, is this a police station?
Yes, it is. How can we help you?

Yeah, okay, I know this sounds ridiculous, but I'm on 24th Street at a car wash, and I'm stuck inside. I put $5 in, it sprayed a soak on me, and now the doors won't open, and I'm scared to get out of the car.
What's the name of the car wash?
It's, um, I don't know. It's on 24th Street. It's next to a party store, I think. I'm really freaked out.
You're on 24th Street? Do you know any other landmarks around there?
Yeah, I'm across from Mueller Brass.
Okay, you're across from Mueller Brass. Hold on just a minute, okay? Please don't hang up.
Alright, thanks.
Hello?
Yeah.
Okay, can you explain again? You can't move your car out?
Yeah, the garage doors are shut on both sides and they're not opening.
Was there anybody working there, or is it one of those self-serve washes?
It's a self-serve. It sprayed a soak on my car, and now nothing else is happening. Both doors are shut.
And you don't know the name of the place at all?
It's something like Super something, I can't remember. I'm across from Mueller Brass and on 24th Street.
And you're in a Jeep, you said? Is it that you can't even see outside?
Yes, I'm in a Jeep, and I'm really freaking out.
Alright. Your call says you're calling from Flint?
No, that's just my cell phone.
Do you have enough battery on your phone?
I have a Boost phone, and I'm about to run out of minutes.
Alright. I'm going to try to help you here. Is everything running inside the car wash, like the equipment?
No, nothing's running.
Can you get out of your car and see if there's a button on the wall that you can push to open the doors? There should be something you can press.
There's a guy behind me. I hope he doesn't start it.
If he starts it, you might be able to get out. But try to see if there's a button inside that can open the doors first.
But if he starts the wash, I'm going to get super soaked.
He should know it's cold, and it won't start immediately. Check for a button on the wall.
Okay. There are seven buttons, but none of them are labeled to open the door.
Alright, we'll try to find you. What's the exact name of the car wash, if you can see it?
It's called Best Auto Wash. B-E-S-T Auto Wash.
Alright. Tell the people outside to call the number on the building so the manager can come and get you out.
I called the number already, and it went to an answering machine.
Leave a message, tell them to get down there. Make sure they understand it's urgent.
I left two messages already. But my minutes are running out.
What's the phone number you called?
I called 929-8889. It was an emergency number.
Alright. We'll try contacting them for you, but there should be a button on the wall to open the doors.
I can't see anything helpful. I'm stuck here.
Okay, get out of your car and try checking the buttons again on the wall. There should be something up there.
I got out of the car now. I already left a message on the machine.
Alright. We will try contacting the owner of the car wash for you, but officers can't come over to break the door to let you out.
Okay.
Good luck. Stay safe.
Alright, bye.
